Settings for Mac OS X, using the commercial IBM xlf Fortran
compiler and either IBM xlC or the gnu gcc compiler.


Requires the following environment settings:

ESMF_COMPILER xlf
ESMF_PREC 32

You can compile the ESMF libraries with either a mix of
xlf and gcc/g++ (the gnu C compilers), or with xlf and xlc/xlc++ 
(the IBM product C/C++ compilers).

To compile with gcc, leave ESMF_C_COMPILER unset.
To compile with xlc/xlc++ set: ESMF_C_COMPILER xlc

